FICTION

A NEW YORK STORY -- In Pete Hamill's FOREVER,=20
Cormac O'Connor arrives in New York from Ireland in 1740=20
and is granted the gift of immortality, provided he never leaves=20
the island of Manhattan. Over the next two-and-a-half centuries,=20
O'Connor watches New York evolve from a wilderness into the=20
city that never sleeps. As he relates in this ESSAY, Hamill=20
finished his latest novel September 10, 2001. One day later,=20
watching his city blow apart, he realized he would have to rewrite=20
the end of the book. We meet the boy Cormac in this EXCERPT.=20

