URBAN GRIT -- In this Q&A, Richard Price explains that his=20
latest novel, SAMARITAN, is "about the Haves reaching out=20
without really understanding what the Have Nots are all about,=20
and the trickiness of trying to connect in a real and=20
meaningful way across the lines of race and class." It's also a=20
riveting mystery, a literary blend of psychological suspense=20
and police procedural. Protagonist Ray Mitchell tells his=20
teenage daughter a story in this EXCERPT.=20

