ART AND LIFE -- Baroque painter Artemisia Gentileschi's sex=20
made her a novelty, a fact that created sensational demand for=20
her work. But her sex also made her vulnerable to criticism,=20
and it prevented her from earning the reputation and lasting=20
legacy afforded to her male peers. In THE PASSION OF ARTEMISIA
(now available in paperback), Susan Vreeland (GIRL IN HYACINTH=20
BLUE) brings this once-lost artist to light. The author talks=20
about her heroine in this INTERVIEW, and she introduces her in=20
this EXCERPT.=20

