NONFICTION

ONE PUNCH -- On December 9, 1977, in the middle of a close=20
National Basketball Association game, Kermit Washington of the=20
Los Angeles Lakers punched Rudy Tomjanovich of the Houston=20
Rockets in the face. The blow nearly killed Tomjanovich, and it=20
profoundly changed the lives of both men. In THE PUNCH, veteran=20
sportswriter John Feinstein deftly weaves stories about both=20
players -- their backgrounds and their lives after the incident=20
-- into a larger story about basketball and how the game=20
changed that night. Read an EXCERPT.=20

The Punch:
http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733984X151952X
