RUGGED INDIVIDUALISM -- One of 2002's best memoirs, Judy=20
Blunt's BREAKING CLEAN, is now available in paperback. Born to=20
a Montana family in 1954, Blunt grew up with horses, an endless=20
view, and an almost inborn understanding of her place on the=20
ranch. The women's liberation movement of the '60s sparked her=20
young imagination, but Blunt banked that fire when she took on=20
the roles of wife and mother. Blunt tells the story of her=20
girlhood, her wifehood, and her decision to strike out on her=20
own. She describes the life of ranch women in an ESSAY, while=20
this EXCERPT conveys the quality of her prose: fierce and wry,=20
haunting and proud.=20

