<BR>
Dear Friend of Borders,<BR>
<BR>
While going through photo albums over the holidays, I stumbled across a col=
umn clipped from my hometown newspaper, dated January 1, 1995. There were p=
hotos of several town citizens with captions declaring each person's New Ye=
ar's resolution. A local real-estate agent wanted to lose 50 pounds by summ=
er. A high-school teacher wanted to spend more time with his own kids. And =
then there's me, grinning cheekily off the page, announcing, "I don't make =
resolutions. I'm perfect." <BR>
<BR>
That statement was only half true. I had given up on New Year's<A HREF=3D"h=
ttp://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733948X151952X"><img src=3D"htt=
p://a676.g.akamaitech.net/f/676/773/30m/images.m0.net/catcontent/borders/ja=
nuary2003/newsletter/goodfat.gif" alt=3D"The Good Fat Cookbook" width=3D"92=
" height=3D"140" vspace=3D"5" hspace=3D"8" align=3D"right" border=3D"0"></A=
> resolutions not because I honestly believed I was perfect, but because, i=
n my experience, they never worked. Now, a few years older and maybe a litt=
le bit wiser, I have learned that a lasting lifestyle overhaul is best buil=
t from small, sustainable changes. Take dieting, for instance. I can't live=
 on cabbage soup. I can, however, forego all kinds of packaged grocery-stor=
e treats. I'm trying to focus on being well, not skinny. I've been studying=
 <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733949X151952X">Th=
e Good Fat Cookbook</A>, in which Fran McCullough asks the sensible questio=
n, "If we've been eating low-fat for 30 years, why haven't we gotten health=
ier?" She doesn't suggest easy answers. Instead, she thoroughly explains th=
e difference between bad fats and essential fats, and she offers recipes ri=
ch in the latter, like this yummy <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp=
?HB7922213127X1733950X151952X">salmon chowder</A>. <BR>
<BR>
So, what are your goals for 2003? Do you want to get fit? Maybe you're reso=
lved to get your financial house in order. Perhaps you'd like to learn to b=
e happier. Whatever your goals for the year ahead, you'll find a wealth of =
resources for smart, meaningful change in our <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0=
=2Enet/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733951X151952X">New Year, New You</A> boutique. =
<BR>
<BR>
And remember: Take it easy. <BR>
<BR>
Happy New Year, <BR>
Jessica Jernigan <BR>
