<B>SCIENCE FICTION & FANTASY</B><BR>
<BR>
<B>THE WHEEL OF TIME KEEPS SPINNING</B> -- At long last, the 10th book in <=
B>Robert Jordan</B>'s Wheel of Time series has arrived. As you might expect=
, <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733973X151952X">C=
rossroads of Twilight</A> picks up where its predecessor, <A HREF=3D"http:/=
/borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733974X151952X">Winter's Heart</A>, =
left off. The lives of many stand at a crossroads as Rand al'Thor struggles=
 to discern friend from foe. Read an <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.=
asp?HB7922213127X1733975X151952X">excerpt</A> from this epic fantasy. <BR>
<BR>
<B>A NEW SERIES FROM GREG KEYES</B> -- Fans of high fantasy should also sit=
 up and take note of a new entry in that arena: <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.=
m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733976X151952X">The Briar King</A>. This novel=
 of magic and politics was penned by <B>Greg Keyes</B>, author of the fanta=
stical alternative-history series The Age of Unreason (which began with <A =
HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733977X151952X">Newton=
's Cannon</A>). Read an <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213=
127X1733978X151952X">interview</A> with Keyes and learn about his many infl=
uences, from Germanic sagas to Shotokan karate. Want to get a monthly dispa=
tch from the worlds of science fiction and fantasy? <A HREF=3D"http://borde=
rs1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733979X151952Xnospam%40mailshell.com">Sig=
n up</A> for Borders Tractor Beam, one of our monthly email newsletters. <B=
R>
