<B>NONFICTION</B><BR>
<BR>
<B>ONE PUNCH</B> -- On December 9, 1977, in the middle of a close National =
Basketball Association game, Kermit Washington of the Los Angeles Lakers pu=
nched Rudy Tomjanovich of the Houston Rockets in the face. The blow nearly =
killed Tomjanovich, and it profoundly changed the lives of both men. In <A =
HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733984X151952X">The Pu=
nch</A>, veteran sportswriter <B>John Feinstein</B> deftly weaves stories a=
bout both players -- their backgrounds and their lives after the incident -=
- into a larger story about basketball and how the game changed that night.=
 Read an <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733985X151=
952X">excerpt</A>. <BR>
<BR>
<B>WHAT KIDS REALLY NEED</B> -- Now available in paperback, <B>Mel Levine</=
B>'s wonderful bestseller, <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922=
213127X1733986X151952X">A Mind at a Time</A>, is based on the deceptively s=
imple premise that different children have different ways of learning. Now,=
 the pediatrician and development expert is back with a new book, <A HREF=
=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733987X151952X">The Myth o=
f Laziness</A>, in which he explores the troubles some teenagers experience=
 in school. <BR>
<BR>
<B>RUGGED INDIVIDUALISM</B> -- One of 2002's best memoirs, <B>Judy Blunt</B=
>'s <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733988X151952X"=
>Breaking Clean</A>, is now available in paperback. Born to a Montana famil=
y in 1954, Blunt grew up with horses, an endless view, and an almost inborn=
 understanding of her place on the ranch. The women's liberation movement o=
f the '60s sparked her young imagination, but Blunt banked that fire when s=
he took on the roles of wife and mother. Blunt tells the story of her girlh=
ood, her wifehood, and her decision to strike out on her own. She describes=
 the life of ranch women in an <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB=
7922213127X1733989X151952X">essay</A>, while this <A HREF=3D"http://borders=
1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733990X151952X">excerpt</A> conveys the qual=
ity of her prose: fierce and wry, haunting and proud. <BR>
