<B>FOOD AND COOKING</B><BR>
<BR>
<B>TALKING WITH PATRICIA WELLS</B> -- Since the publication of <A HREF=3D"h=
ttp://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733998X151952X">Bistro Cooking<=
/A>, <B>Patricia Wells</B> has been a household name for foodies around the=
 world. Wells divides her time between Paris and Provence, and her experien=
ce as a passionate expatriate provides inspiration for her cookbooks. In th=
is <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1733999X151952X">=
article</A>, we talk to Wells about French flavors and attitudes, and we as=
k her to recommend some cookbooks that have an honored place in her own kit=
chen. Try her recipe for <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB792221=
3127X1734000X151952X">Gallopin's Green Bean, Mushroom, and Hazelnut Salad</=
A> from <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734001X1519=
52X">The Paris Cookbook</A>. <BR>
<BR>
<B>SANE NUTRITION</B> -- In <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB792=
2213127X1734002X151952X">The Get with the Program! Guide to Good Eating</A>=
, celebrity trainer <B>Bob Greene</B> offers in-depth nutrition information=
 and recipes that fit into his inspirational fitness plan. He recommends po=
sitive lifestyle changes, not get-thin-quick schemes, and he recognizes tha=
t enjoyment is an important element of eating. Greene doesn't banish fat, w=
hich adds flavor and creates a pleasant sense of satiety. Instead, he inclu=
des fat in its most healthful forms. <BR>
<BR>
<B>SOPHISTICATED PALATE</B> -- For 23 years, chef <B>Judy Rodgers</B> has b=
een bewitching diners with honest, elegant food. In <A HREF=3D"http://borde=
rs1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734003X151952X">The Zuni Caf=E9 Cookbook</=
A>, she presents recipes for a host of signature dishes, including her worl=
d-famous Zuni Roast Chicken and other French- and Mediterranean-inspired fa=
re. Enriched with the wisdom of a master chef but accessible even to the no=
vice cook, this beautifully written cookbook offers pleasures for the mind =
as well as the palate. <BR>
