<B>POP AND MORE</B><BR>
<BR>
<B>ROLLING ROCK</B> -- Capturing the brilliance of <B>Bob Dylan</B>'s stint=
 as the leader of <B>The Rolling Thunder Revue</B>, the long-anticipated <A=
 HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734010X151952X">Live =
1975</A> is the fifth installment in the Bootleg series. Packaged with a li=
mited-edition DVD, the album brings together the finest tracks from four li=
ve performances. The two-CD set includes well-known tunes such as "Blowin' =
in the Wind" and less familiar songs like "Mama, You Been on My Mind." <BR>
<BR>
<B>PHISH HOOKS</B> -- Just two years after stunning fans with the news that=
 they were going on indefinite hiatus, jam masters <B>Phish</B> return with=
 <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734011X151952X">Ro=
und Room</A>, a studio release that adroitly captures all the energy of the=
 band's fabled live shows. Fresh off a multitude of side projects, the tigh=
t-knit quartet sounds refreshed and ready, gleefully performing high-energy=
 grooves and whimsical lyrics on such memorably named tracks as "Mock Song"=
 and "Thunderhead." <BR>
<BR>
<B>EXPANDED ELVIS</B> -- Boasting extensive new liner notes, previously unr=
eleased material, rare photos, and printed song lyrics, the latest trio of =
two-disc <B>Elvis Costello</B> reissues includes 1979's <A HREF=3D"http://b=
orders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734012X151952X">Armed Forces</A> (incl=
uding nine tracks taken from a 1978 concert at Hollywood High School), 1982=
's <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734013X151952X">=
Imperial Bedroom</A> (originally recorded by Beatles engineer Geoff Emerick=
), and 1991's <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X173401=
4X151952X">Mighty Like a Rose</A> (featuring numerous demos and unplugged v=
ersions). These recordings wonderfully document distinct phases in the care=
er of this most eclectic performer. <BR>
<BR>
<B>THE PRESLEY PAGES</B> -- In <B>Bobbie Ann Mason</B>'s <A HREF=3D"http://=
borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734015X151952X">Elvis Presley</A>, a =
great Southern writer takes on the phenomenon of the King, from his explosi=
on onto the American pop stage to his lonely, final years at Graceland. Rea=
d Mason's <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734016X15=
1952X">introduction</A>; then be sure to check out the new collection of El=
vis's biggest smashes: <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB79222131=
27X1734017X151952X">Elvis: 30 #1 Hits</A>. Also, read our Jessica Jernigan'=
s <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734018X151952X">t=
houghts on Elvis</A>, occasioned by reading Mason's book and listening to t=
he music. <BR>
<BR>
<B>ALISON WONDERLAND</B> -- Performing 25 of their best-loved numbers befor=
e an enthusiastic Louisville audience on the two-disc <A HREF=3D"http://bor=
ders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734019X151952X">Live</A>, Alison Krauss =
& Union Station shine on crowd favorites like the rousing "Oh, Atlanta" and=
 the tender "Baby, Now That I've Found You." The album is bursting with eng=
aging vocals and instrumental fireworks, and Krauss and company also offer =
up a scorching rendition of "I Am a Man of Constant Sorrow." Check out more=
 great <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734020X15195=
2X">Bluegrass, Country & Folk music</A>. <BR>
<BR>
<B>CLASSICAL MUSIC</B><BR>
<BR>
<B>PIANO PERSPECTIVES</B> -- A splendid compilation featuring two CDs worth=
 of Mitsuko Uchida's most exhilarating keyboard performances, <A HREF=3D"ht=
tp://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734021X151952X">Perspectives</A>=
 contains a veritable treasure trove of musical highlights. Among them are =
the eclectic Japanese pianist's dazzling renditions of works by Debussy, Mo=
zart, Beethoven, and Schubert. Check out other indispensable instrumental a=
nd vocal performances in the <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB79=
22213127X1734022X151952X">Borders Classical Essentials Catalog</A>. <BR>
<BR>
<B>GRAND GROBAN</B> -- <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB79222131=
27X1734023X151952X">In Concert</A>, the first live release from classical v=
ocalist <B>Josh Groban</B>, captures the 21-year-old star casting a spell o=
ver a Pasadena, California, audience. With pieces taken from the PBS progra=
m <I>Great Performances</I>, the CD includes seven tunes sung from the stag=
e, plus "O Holy Night." The bonus DVD features the entire 15-song performan=
ce and behind-the-scenes footage. <BR>
