<B>STAKE AND SHAKE</B> -- She's anything but your typical high-school beaut=
y queen: She's a vampire's worst nightmare. Heartthrob Sarah Michelle Gella=
r stars on the recently released <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?=
HB7922213127X1734032X151952X">Buffy the Vampire Slayer: The Complete Third =
Season</A>, which features more of the series' blend of humor and bewitchin=
g story lines. In addition to all 22 episodes, the six-DVD box contains fiv=
e featurettes, commentary from creator Joss Whedon, and more. Check out oth=
er <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734033X151952X">=
TV favorites on DVD</A>. <BR>
<BR>
<B>SIGNS OF THE TIMES</B> -- Mixing elements of 1950s sci-fi with the quiet=
 terror that permeated his <I>The Sixth Sense</I>, visionary director M. Ni=
ght Shyamalan presents the taut thriller <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/=
m/s.asp?HB7922213127X1734034X151952X">Signs</A>. Mel Gibson plays a disillu=
sioned priest who turns to farming and discovers crop circles -- and then s=
omething much more ominous -- in his cornfields. Also starring Joaquin Phoe=
nix and Rory Culkin. The DVD includes five deleted scenes and an in-depth, =
six-part documentary that explores the making of the movie. <BR>
<BR>
<B>GOOD AND BORED</B> -- In a refreshing, compelling performance, Jennifer =
Aniston is the pretty but completely unglamorous star of the acclaimed, ind=
ependent black comedy <A HREF=3D"http://borders1.m0.net/m/s.asp?HB792221312=
7X1734035X151952X">The Good Girl</A>. She plays Justine, a retail clerk bor=
ed with both her dead-end job and childless marriage who begins a passionat=
e affair with her much younger coworker, Holden (Jake Gyllenhaal). Also sta=
rring John C. Reilly and Tim Blake Nelson. The DVD includes commentary by A=
niston, deleted scenes, and gag and outtake reels. <BR>
